HEADWORD: Inerrable
<hw>In*er"ra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inerrabilis</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and <er>Err</er>.]</ety>
<def>Incapable of erring; infallible; unerring.</def>
